Welcome to the Fourth Workshop on End-User Software Engineering. WEUSE IV is a one-day workshop aimed at challenges faced in helping end users develop dependable software. 
 
WEUSE IV is structured around four themes. Each of the twenty short papers accepted to the workshop has overlap with one or more of the following themes: 
Empirical Evaluation in End-User Software Engineering 
Learning from End Users 
Software Engineering for End Users 
End-User Tools for Creating Dependable Software 
 
 
 
Each theme will be introduced by a session lead who will set forth his or her vision in the theme area, taking into account relevant papers. Following each presentation, there will be ample time for discussion.